    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters April 16th with a lineup optimized to exploit favorable matchups against a collection of suspect starters. The standout play of the day is **Tyler Soderstrom**, who boasts the highest efficiency score (76.91) thanks to a lucrative combination of a hitter-friendly venue, a generous matchup against Leiter, and the stability of the cleanup spot. Close behind, **Vinnie Pasquantino** (76.21) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.75) are elite starts; **Mickey Moniak** specifically benefits from an immense +19% boost from the opposing pitcher\u2019s skill profile and a +14% platoon edge against Ryan Weiss. While **Josh Naylor** (74.81) faces a stiffer test in Walker Buehler, the SP skill variance and batting order protection keep him firmly in the \"Strong\" start tier, serving as a pillar for our RBI production today.\n\nThe lineup prioritizes aggressive base-running dynamics, particularly with **Brice Turang** (64.27) and **Jose Caballero** (66.69). **Brice Turang** is a priority play due to his high-leverage spot in the #2 hole and a favorable +4% efficiency boost stemming from the pitcher's slow delivery, which significantly improves his probability of a stolen base. While **James Wood** (55.43) remains a marginal start, his projection is hampered by an elite-level hold rate from the opposing pitcher, limiting his stolen base upside today. **Kyle Karros** (50.77) was the closest to the bench; he only retains his spot because the matchup against Ryan Weiss is sufficiently soft to justify the risk, even with the downside of the #8 hole. We are currently navigating a thin bench as **Corbin Carroll**, **Austin Riley**, **Seiya Suzuki**, and **Trevor Story** are all unavailable today due to team off-days, leaving us with minimal flexibility to rotate in reserves like **Gabriel Moreno**, **Max Muncy**, **Dalton Rushing**, **Zach McKinstry**, **Alex Freeland**, **Carson Williams**, or **Travis Bazzana**. Monitor the status of **Luis Campusano** and **Kyle Karros** closely, as their scores are contingent on the unconfirmed batting orders; should either drop lower in the lineup, we will be forced to reconsider their utility.",
